    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="80"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00/18½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">12 March, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I wish you would be kind enough
                    to formulate a careful and conclusive memorandum for the use of the committee of
                    the Senate with regard to the enclosed resolution.<note n="81" xml:id="d80fn1"
                        >For text of resolution, see enclosure to the following document.</note> I
                    take it for granted that you feel as I do that this is no time to act as the
                    resolution prescribes, and certainly when I pronounced for open diplomacy, I
                    meant not that there should be no private discussions <pb facs="0159" n="113"
                        xml:id="pg_113"/> of delicate matters, but that no secret agreements of any
                    sort should be entered into and that all international relations, when fixed,
                    should be open, above-board, and explicit.</p>
                <p>Cordially and sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
